name: institutionCode
description: The Index Herbariorum code for the herbarium supplying the record.

name: collectionCode
description: An acronym or code of a collection or source within the institution.
comments: May be the same as institutionCode

name: modified
description: Date and time of the last modification to any component of the record.
usage: Must  be an ISO 8601:2004(E) date or (preferrably) date and time.

name: basisOfRecord
description: Nature of the record

name: type
description: Nature of the resource

name: language
description: Language of the resource
comments: For multimedia objects dcterms:language strictly speaking is the language of the resource. Audubon Core has a separate element, ac:metadataLanguage, to transfer the language of the metadata.

name: rightsHolder
description: [The name of] Owner of the copyright over the resource.

name: license
description: URL defining or elaborating on the licence statement.

name: informationWithheld
description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.
examples: "location information not given for endangered species", "collector identities withheld", "ask about tissue samples"

name: dataGeneralizations
description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.
examples: "Coordinates generalized from original GPS coordinates to the nearest half degree grid cell".

name: occurrenceID
description: A globally unique identifier for the collection object record.
usage: Preferrably use a UUID. If this is not feasible an identifier can be created based on a unique field in the database, for example the catalogNumber. If doing so, the identifier must be stored in the database and cannot be changed or used for another record.

name: catalogNumber
description: The unique identifier for each collection object, including the acronym

name: recordedBy
description: The name(s) of the person or persons who made the collection on which this record is based
usage: Any valid collector's name, collector's family name (surname) followed by comma and space (", ") then initials (all in uppercase and separated by fullstops).
comments: The format of names is not strictly enforced, but when available should be provided in the standard form.
examples: "Steenis, C.G.G.J. van", "Wilson, Peter G.", "Streimann, H.|Mundua, A."

name: recordNumber
description: The verbatim collecting number

name: preparations
description: List of preparations from a specimen

name: otherCatalogNumbers
description: A list of previous or alternate catalog numbers for the same Occurrence.
usage: e.g., for the catalogue numbers for exchanged specimens when known or of multisheets.
comments: Note - this is a broader definition than implied by the HISPID 3 mapping

name: occurrenceRemarks
description: Any additional information provided by the collector.
usage: This may contain information about the collecting event/gathering, or descriptive information about the organism.
comments: Darwin Core maps occurrenceRemarks to abcd://Unit/Notes and eventRemarks to abcd://Unit/Gathering/Remarks, but botanical collecting notes often contain descriptive notes, which relate to a taxon and hence semantically fit better in occurrenceRemarks. At the same time, they fit better in abcd://Unit/Gathering/Notes, to which they were mapped in HISPID 5, in order to distinguish between notes made by the collector in the field and which refer to the Occurrence and annotations that are made in the herbarium and which refer to the PreservedSpecimen, i.e. abcd://Unit/Notes or HISPID Miscellaneous Notes (misc).

name: organismQuantity
description: An indication of abundance of the taxon at the collecting locality as recorded by the collector
usage: The value should be from "Tansley (1946) scale"
comments: organismQuantityType  must be delivered alongside this term. Note that this is a considerable deviation from earlier versions of HISPID, where Frequency was a free text field.

name: organismQuantityType
description: The type of entity to which the number or enumeration value reported for the quantity of organisms in organismQuantity refers

name: establishmentMeans
description: The process by which the individual(s) represented in the Occurrence became established at the location.

name: lifeForm
description: A description of the habit or life form of the specimen on which the collection object is based.

name: lifeStage
description: The life stage of the individual at the time it was collected.

name: sex
description: The sex of the individual

name: reproductiveCondition
description: Reproductive condition(s) of the individual represented by the collection object.

name: associatedTaxa
description: A list of names of taxa and their associations with the Occurrence.
comments: The ABCD mapping using the Synecology element can only be used to transfer one association type, 'growingWith'.  Host taxa have to be delivered using a MeasurementOrFact. The HISPID 5 free text representation cannot be delivered in this element at all and needs to be delivered as part of habitat.

name: associationType
description: Type of association
usage: To be used in combination with dwc:Taxon to make up list for associatedTaxa
comments: Could potentially be used for dwc:associatedOccurrences as well, in combination with a dwc:Occurrence.

name: associatedSequences
description: List of identifiers for sequences associated with the collection object.
usage: Use Genbank accession numbers.

name: disposition
description: Current state of the specimen with respect to the collection identified by the collectionCode and institutionCode.

name: eventID
description: An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time).
usage: May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

name: parentEventID
description: An identifier for the broader Event that groups this and potentially other Events.
usage: May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set. Must be an existing EventID. Could be used for collecting trips and expeditions.

name: habitat
description: Description of the habitat from where the collection object was collected, including geology and soil type, as well as the associated species.

name: topography
description: A description of the topography of the habitat from which the collection object was collected

name: aspect
description: The abbreviated aspect or outlook of the site from which the collection object was gathered.

name: geologicalSubstrate
description: The substrate or parent rock material in the habitat from which the collection object was collected.

name: substrate
description: The material from which the collection object was collected.

name: soil
description: Description of the surface soil type from which the collection object was collected.

name: vegetation
description: Description of the vegetation from which the specimen was collected.

name: eventDate
description: The date or period when the specimen was collected

name: verbatimEventDate
description: The verbatim date information of when the specimen was collected

name: collectingTrip
description: The collecting trip or expedition where the specimen was collected

name: locality
description: Description of the locality from where the specimen was collected.

name: verbatimLocality
description: Verbatim locality description
usage: Locality should always be delivered; only deliver verbatimLocality if stored separately from the locality.

name: continent
description: The name of the continent in which the collecting locality is situated.

name: country
description: The name of the country in which the collecting locality is situated
comments: This may not reflect the currently political boundaries

name: countryCode
description: The standard ISO-3166 code for the country in which the collecting locality is situated.

name: stateProvince
description: The name of the next smaller administrative region after country in which the collecting locality is situated.

name: county
description: The name of the next smaller administrative region after stateProvince in which the collecting locality is situated.

name: waterBody
description: The name of the water body in which the Location occurs.

name: islandGroup
description: The name of the island group in which the Location occurs.

name: island
description: The name of the island on or near which the Location occurs.

name: decimalLatitude
description: The geographic latitude of the collecting locality

name: decimalLongitude
description: The geodetic longitude of the collecting locality

name: geodeticDatum
description: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geographic coordinates given in decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude are based.
usage: Use of EPSG codes is recommended.

name: verbatimLatitude
description: The verbatim original latitude for the Location
usage: The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

name: verbatimLongitude
description: The verbatim original longitude for the Location
usage: The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

name: verbatimCoordinates
description: The verbatim original geographic coordinates for the Location
usage: Use for UTM type coordinates. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

name: verbatimCoordinateSystem
description: The spatial coordinate system for the verbatimLatitude and verbatimLongitude or the verbatimCoordinates of the Location.
usage: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

name: verbatimSRS
description: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which coordinates given in verbatimLatitude and verbatimLongitude, or verbatimCoordinates are based
usage: Recommended best practice is use the EPSG code as a controlled vocabulary to provide an SRS, if know

name: coordinatePrecision
description: A decimal representation of the precision of the coordinates given in the decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude

name: coordinateUncertaintyInMeters
description: Estimate of the maximum horizontal distance between the point referenced by the decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude and the actual location the collection took place.
comments: Historically many Australian herbaria have used classes to record the uncertainty in meters, for example 0–50 m, 50–1000 m, 1000–10000 m, 10000–25000 m, > 25000 m. The upper limit of these classes is delivered as coordinateUncertainty.

name: georeferencedBy
description: Name(s) of person(s), group(s) or organisation(s) who took the georeference of the Location

name: georeferenceProtocol
description: A description of or reference to the methods used to determine the geographic coordinates of the Location.

name: georeferencedDate
description: The date on which the Location was georeferenced.
usage: Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

name: georeferenceSources
description: A list of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference the Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resource.

name: georeferenceVerificationStatus
description: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial descript
usage: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

name: georeferenceRemarks
description: Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalised in the method referred to in georeferenceProtocol.

name: nearestNamedPlace
description: The nearest named place to the collecting locality.
comments: We do not want to use this as generalised locality any more. There are still two use cases: (1) a nearest named placed given by a collector when the collecting locality doesn't have a name or is obscure and (2) the place name the georeference is based on when the name of the locality can't be found in any gazetteer. The latter use case probably desrves its own term.

name: minimumElevationInMeters
description: Elevation or lower value of a range of elevation in metres.

name: maximumElevationInMeters
description: Higher value of the range of elevation in metres.

name: verbatimElevation
description: The original description of the elevation as provided by the collector.

name: elevationMethod
description: Method by which the elevation was determined.

name: minimumDepthInMeters
description: Depth or the lesser of a range of depth below the local surface in metres.

name: maximumDepthInMeters
description: The greater of a range of depths below the local surface in metres.

name: verbatimDepth
description: Verbatim description of the depth, as provided by the collector.

name: identificationID
description: Identifier for the Identification
usage: Use of a UUID is recommended.

name: identificationQualifier
description: A brief phrase or standard term to express doubt about an identification.

name: identificationQualifierRank
description: Rank at which the identificationQualifier applies

name: nameAddendum
description: A suffix added after the scientific name to indicate aggregate taxa or  more or less inclusive taxon concepts

name: identificationVerificationStatus
description: Verification status of the identification, or an indication of how reliable the identification is deemed to be.

name: identifierRole
description: Categorical indicator of the type of contribution made by the determiner.

name: identifiedBy
description: The name(s) of people, groups, or organisations who  identified the collection object.

name: dateIdentified
description: The date on which the collection object was identified.

name: verbatimDateIdentified
description: The verbatim date of the Identification.

name: identificationReferences
description: References used for the Identification.

name: previousIdentifications
description: Previous identifications of the collection object.
usage: It is preferrable to use the repeatable Identification elements in ABCD or the Identification extension in Darwin Core.

name: identificationRemarks
description: Any additional comments made by the determiner as part of the Identification.

name: typeStatusQualifier
description: Standard term to qualify the type status designation.

name: typeStatus
description: Code indicating the type status of the collection object.
comments: typeStatus has been placed in the HISPID namespace, even though it is available in Darwin Core, because our use is different. In contrast to Darwin Core, in HISPID typeStatus and typifiedName have been separated. Having typeStatus in the HISPID namespace allows us to transfer the type status including or excluding the typified name depending on what circumstances require.

name: typifiedName
description: The scientific name of which the collection object is a type.

name: taxonRank
description: Taxonomic rank of the taxon to which the collection object has been identified.

name: kingdom
description: Full scientific name of the kingdom in which the taxon is classified

name: phylum
description: Full scientific name of the phylum in which the taxon is classified

name: class
description: Full scientific name of the class in which the taxon is classified

name: order
description: Full scientific name of the order in which the taxon is classified

name: family
description: Full scientific name of the order in which the family is classified

name: genus
description: Full scientific name of the order in which the genus is classified

name: specificEpithet
description: Species epithet of the scientific name.

name: infraspecificEpithet
description: Infraspecific epithet of the scientific name.

name: scientificNameID
description: An identifier for the nomenclatural (not taxonomic) details of a scientific name.

name: scientificName
description: Full scientific name with authorship

name: scientificNameAuthorship
description: Authorship of the scientific name formatted to the conventions of the applicable nomenclatural code.
comments: The parsing of the authorship into the authorship of the basionym and of the combination, as ABCD does, is discouraged. Also in ABCD the entire authorship should be delivered in AuthorTeam.

name: nomenclaturalCode
description: Nomenclatural code under which the scientific name is applied.

name: vernacularName
description: A vernacular name assigned to the specimen.
comments: Only use when provided by the collector, e.g. when the collection is a result of ethnobotanical study.

name: cultivarGroupName
description: Cultivar group name
usage: Follow the conventions in the ICNCP.

name: cultivarName
description: Cultivar name
usage: Follow the conventions in the ICNCP.

name: tradeDesignation
description: Trade designation
usage: Follow the conventions in the ICNCP.

name: hybridFlag
description: Flag to indicate whether the plant name refers to a hybrid, graft chimaera or intergrade, without reference to rank.
comments: The ABCD and HISPID 5 //Unit/Identifications/Identification/Result/TaxonIdentified/ScientificName/NameAtomised/Botanical/HybridFlag only applies to hybrid names (hybridFlag:"x").

name: hybridParent1
description: Scientific name of the first parent of a hybrid

name: hybridParent2
description: Scientific name of the second parent of a hybrid

name: miscellaneousRemarks
description: Any additional information to be transferred pertaining to the collection object.

name: exsiccataSeries
description: Exsiccata series

name: exsiccataFascicle
description: Fascicle in exsiccata series

name: exsiccataNumber
description: Number in exsiccata series

name: voucherFor
description: Term to indicate the collection object has served as a voucher for a special purpose.

name: provenanceTypeFlag
description: Code to indicate the type of provenance of the cultivated material from which this collection object was taken.
usage: Use ITF2 codes

name: cultivatedPlantProvenance
description: Descriptive and coded information that describes the geographic position from which the source material of the cultivated plant from which the collection object was taken was collected.
usage: Preferrably this information is databased and delivered as a related resource, using all relevant elements from the relevant standard; if this is not feasible, the information can be delivered as free text, providing as much detail as possible.

name: donor
description: The person, business or institution from which the collection object was obtained.

name: duplicatesDistributedTo
description: List of institutions replicates have been sent to.
usage: Use Index Herbariorum acronyms.

name: loanIdentifier
description: The number assigned to the loan by the lending institution.

name: loanDestination
description: Institution to which the loan is sent.
usage: Preferrably an Index Herbriorum acronym is used.

name: loanForBotanist
description: Name(s) of the botanist(s) for whom the loan is intended.

name: loanDate
description: The date the loan is prepared and/or sent.

name: loanReturnDate
description: The date the loan is due to be returned.

name: permitType
description: Type of permit.

name: permitReferenceNumber
description: Reference number allocated to the permit by the issuing authority.

name: permitIssuedBy
description: Name of the authority by whom the permit was issued.

name: permitIssuedTo
description: Name(s) of the person(s) or organisation to whom the permit was issued.

name: permitIssuedDate
description: Date the permit was issued.

name: permitValidDate
description: Date or period for which the permit is valid.

name: permitStatus
description: Status of the permit.

name: permitConditions
description: Conditions on the permit, which may affect how the specimens collected under the permit may be used or distributed.

name: permitRemarks
description: Any additional comments pertaining to the permit.

name: permitLink
description: The link to an electronic version of the permit.

name: creator
description: Creator of the media object.

name: createDate
description: Date the media object, or its source, was created.

name: digitizationDate
description: Date the media object was created.

name: source
description: Original source of the media object, if the resource was digitised from a non-digital source.

name: title
description: Title of the media object, including subtitles, if any.

name: description
description: Description of the media resource.

name: caption
description: Free-form text to be displayed together with (rather than instead of) a media object that is suitable for captions.

name: physicalSetting
description: The setting of the content represented in the media object

name: subjectCategory
description: Broad subject or context of the media object.

name: tag
description: Tag or keyword.

name: subjectPart
description: Part of the subject that is imaged.

name: subjectOrientation
description: Orientation of the subject represented in the media object with respect to the capturing device.

name: captureDevice
description: Device used to create the media object.

name: resourceCreationTechnique
description: Information about technical aspects of the creation of the media object.

name: relatedResourceID
description: Identifier(s) of related media objects, e.g.different view angles of the same subject.

name: mediaItemID
description: An arbitrary code that is unique for the resource, with the resource being either a provider, collection, or media item

name: subtype
description: Any URI may be used that provides for more specialization than the type. Possible values are community-defined.
usage: URI to vocabulary term
vocabulary: Drawing, Painting, Logo, Icon, Illustration, Graphic, Photograph, Animation, Film, SlideShow, DesignPlan, Diagram, Map, MusicalNotation, IdentificationKey, ScannedText, RecordedText, RecordedOrganism, TaxonPage, MultimediaLearningObject, VirtualRealityEnvironment, GlossaryPage.

name: metadataDate
description: Point in time recording when the last modification to metadata (not necessarily the media object itself) occurred.

name: providerManagedID
description: A free-form identifier (a simple number, an alphanumeric code, a URL, etc.) that is unique and meaningful primarily for the data provider.

name: available
description: The date (often a range) that the resource became or will become available.

name: hasServiceAccessPoint
description: Service access point for metadata about this media resource

name: rights
description: Information about rights held in and over the resource.

name: licenseTerms
description: The license statement defining how resources may be used.

name: licenseURL
description: A URL defining or further elaborating on the license statement (e. g., a web page explaining the precise terms of use).

name: licenseLogoURL
description: A URL providing access to a logo that symbolizes the License.

name: credit
description: Attribution statement

name: attributionURL
description: The URL of the icon or logo image to appear in source attribution.

name: attributionLinkURL
description: The URL where information about ownership, attribution, etc. of the resource may be found.

name: funding
description: Organizations or individuals who funded the creation of the resource.

name: provider
description: Person or organization responsible for presenting the media resource.

name: subjectCategoryVocabulary
description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.

name: taxonCoverage
description: A higher taxon (e. g., a genus, family, or order) at the level of the genus or higher, that covers all taxa that are the primary subject of the resource

name: derivedFrom
description: A reference to an original resource from which the current one is derived.

name: associatedSpecimenReference
description: A reference to a specimen associated with this resource.
usage: This should be in the same form as catalogNumber

name: associatedObservationReference
description: A reference to an observation associated with this resource.

name: accessURI
description: A URI that uniquely identifies a service that provides a representation of the underlying resource. If this resource can be acquired by an http request, its http URL should be given. If not, but it has some URI in another URI scheme, that may be given here.

name: format
description: A string describing the technical format of the resource (file format or physical medium).
comments: maybe be more appropriate to use  dcterms:format?

name: variant
description: A URI designating what this Service Access Point provides. Some suggested values are the URIs ac:Thumbnail, ac:Trailer, ac:LowerQuality, ac:MediumQuality, ac:GoodQuality, ac:BestQuality, and ac:Offline. Additional URIs from communities of practice may be introduced.

name: furtherInformationURL
description: The URL of a Web site that provides additional information about the version of the media resource that is provided by the Service Access Point.
